
[1]monstrously

   MON'STROUSLY, adv. In a manner out of the common order of nature;
   hence, shockingly; terribly; hideously; horribly; as a man monstrously
   wicked.

   1. To a great degree; enormously; extravagantly.

   Who with his wife is monstrously in love.
